# 💸 Cash Journal – AI-Driven Personal Finance Diary

A personal finance diary and budgeting web app designed to help users become more conscious of their spending habits, reduce impulsive purchases, and gain insights through AI-powered categorization and forecasting.

---

## ✅ Core Functionalities

### 👤 User Authentication
- Sign up and log in using Django’s built-in auth system

### 🏠 Homepage
- Dashboard-style entry point to navigate the app

### 📅 Finance Calendar / Journal
- Log purchases by date
- Attach notes, reflections, or receipts to transactions

### 🎯 Wishlist Page
- Add items to a wishlist
- Helps delay impulse spending and track future wants

### 📊 Spending Tracker
- Categorize and view spending
- Filter by category, date, or amount

### ⚙️ Account & Settings
- Manage user preferences and personal data

### 🧠 AI Features

#### 📌 NLP Categorization
- Automatically categorize transactions based on their description using an NLP model
- Example: `"Uber trip"` → `Transport`

#### 📈 Spending Forecast (Regression)
- Predict upcoming monthly or weekly expenses based on historical data
- Example: "Based on your last 3 months, you’re likely to spend £450 in April."

---

## 🧱 Tech Stack

| Layer        | Technology                      | Purpose                                        |
|--------------|----------------------------------|------------------------------------------------|
| **Frontend** | HTML, CSS, JavaScript           | Static pages for UI and interactions           |
| **Backend**  | Django (Python)                 | Core logic, API endpoints, and auth            |
| **Database** | PostgreSQL (Heroku Add-on)      | Stores transactions, users, wishlist, etc.     |
| **ML/NLP**   | Scikit-learn, Pandas (Python)   | Categorization + Regression forecasting        |
| **Auth**     | Django built-in authentication  | Handles login, registration, sessions          |
| **Styling**  | Vanilla CSS                     | Simple responsive layout                       |
| **Deployment** | **Heroku**                    | Hosts backend + static frontend (via Django)   |

